57#include <openssl/x509.h>
58
59#include <string.h>
60
61#include <openssl/asn1.h>
62#include <openssl/err.h>
63#include <openssl/mem.h>
64#include <openssl/thread.h>
65
66
67X509_PKEY *X509_PKEY_new(void)
68 {
69 X509_PKEY *ret = OPENSSL_malloc(sizeof(X509_PKEY));
70 if (ret == NULL)
71 {
72 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
73 goto err;
74 }
75 memset(ret, 0, sizeof(X509_PKEY));
76
77 ret->enc_algor = X509_ALGOR_new();
78 if (ret->enc_algor == NULL)
79 goto err;
80 ret->enc_pkey = M_ASN1_OCTET_STRING_new();
81 if (ret->enc_pkey == NULL)
82 goto err;
83 return ret;
84
85err:
86 if (ret != NULL)
87 X509_PKEY_free(ret);
88 return NULL;
89 }
90
91void X509_PKEY_free(X509_PKEY *x)
92 {
93 if (x == NULL) return;
94
95 if (x->enc_algor != NULL) X509_ALGOR_free(x->enc_algor);
96 if (x->enc_pkey != NULL) M_ASN1_OCTET_STRING_free(x->enc_pkey);
97 if (x->dec_pkey != NULL)EVP_PKEY_free(x->dec_pkey);
98 if ((x->key_data != NULL) && (x->key_free)) OPENSSL_free(x->key_data);
99 OPENSSL_free(x);
100 }
